com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport

Class Property

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.CoreProperty
      • com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.Property
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IIdentifiable

    public final class Property
extends CoreProperty
    A simple property of a particular property type.

    A Property holds a single data value. It may be contained within a PropertyGroup, or directly within a Card on an Item.

    Throughout its lifetime, a property is subject to validation rules:

    • If the property is contained within a PropertyGroup, then its PropertyType must correspond to one in the PropertyGroupType of its enclosing PropertyGroup.
    • If the property is contained directly within a Card, then its PropertyType must correspond to one in the ItemType of the Item that owns the Card.
    • See CoreProperty for more validation rules.
    Since:
    1.0
